378.caption: Criticality
378.description: Defines if and when notifications are sent. A = 7x24, B = 5x12, C = never. Host criticality limits what its services can send. For example, given a host with criticality B, if a service with criticality A has a problem, the notification will only be sent during 5x12.

744.caption: HTTP: Certificate
744.description: Minimum number of days a certificate has to be valid. This parameter explicitely sets the port to 443 and ignores the URL if passed.

745.caption: HTTP: Client Cert
745.description: Name of file contains the client certificate (PEM format)

747.caption: HTTP: Critical Time
747.description: Response time to result in critical status (seconds)

748.caption: HTTP: Expect
748.description: Comma-delimited list of strings, at least one of them is expected in the first (status) line of the server response

751.caption: HTTP: Header
751.description: Any other tags to be sent in http header

752.caption: HTTP: Header String
752.description: String to expect in the response headers

753.caption: HTTP: Max Age
753.description: Warn if document is more than seconds old

755.caption: HTTP: Method
755.description: Set http method (for example: HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE)

757.caption: HTTP: Page Size
757.description: Minimum page size required:Maximum page size required

759.caption: HTTP: Private Key
759.description: Name of file contains the private key (PEM format)

760.caption: HTTP: Proxy Auth
760.description: Username:password on proxy-servers with basic authentication

762.caption: HTTP: Useragent
762.description: String to be sent in http header as User Agent

763.caption: HTTP: Warning Time
763.description: Response time to result in warning status (seconds)

764.caption: HTTP: Invert Regex?
764.description: Return CRITICAL if found, OK if not

765.caption: HTTP: Ignore Body?
765.description: Don't wait for document body: stop reading after headers
